  <habitat>seashores</habitat>
  <habitat>plains</habitat>
  <habitat>hills</habitat>
  <habitat>and mountains</habitat>
  <elevation>80–1200 m;</elevation>
  <introduced>introduced;</introduced>
  <us_distribution>Fla.</us_distribution>
  <us_distribution>Ga.</us_distribution>
  <us_distribution>Mass.</us_distribution>
  <us_distribution>N.C.</us_distribution>
  <us_distribution>Wis.</us_distribution>
  <global_distribution>Eurasia.</global_distribution>
  <discussion>Crepis foetida is polymorphic; it is recognized by its annual or biennial habit, usually erect and hispid or setose stems, sharply runcinate leaves, hispid or setose involucres, and dimorphic cypselae.</discussion>
</treatment>

